## Writing New Tests

### Adding Unit Tests

```python
# unit/test_new_feature.py
import pytest
from open_webui.utils.images.your_module import YourClass

@pytest.mark.unit
class TestNewFeature:
    """Test new feature"""
    
    @pytest.mark.asyncio
    async def test_basic_functionality(self):
        """Test basic functionality"""
        obj = YourClass()
        result = await obj.process()
        assert result is not None
```

### Adding Integration Tests

```python
# integration/test_new_integration.py
import pytest
from open_webui.utils.images.prompt_analyzer import PromptAnalyzer

@pytest.mark.integration
class TestNewIntegration:
    """Test integration with external service"""
    
    @pytest.mark.asyncio
    async def test_service_integration(self, mock_service):
        """Test service integration"""
        analyzer = PromptAnalyzer()
        result = await analyzer.analyze("test")
        assert result["status"] == "success"
```

### Using Fixtures

Common fixtures available in `conftest.py`:

```python
def test_with_fixtures(
    mock_openai_client,      # Mocked OpenAI client
    mock_fal_client,         # Mocked Fal client
    mock_database,           # Mocked database
    sample_prompts,          # Sample test prompts
    performance_metrics      # Expected performance metrics
):
    # Your test code
    pass
```

